    <section xml:id='tests-PREFIX-FUNCTIONS'>
      <title>Prefix Functions</title>
      <para>An operation is a sequence of operands that evaluates to a single value.
        Each operand is an expression optionally followed by member access. An operation ends with a colon, a line break,
        or anything which is not an expression. Evaluation uses a context which is empty at the start of an operation.
        When the context is empty, operator-shaped identifiers act as prefix functions, taking the next operand as their argument.</para>
